## ததஅக

[ kāppukkṭṭ ]  
  
inf. to tie a string on the arm in token of vow  
and as a pledge for its performance  
2. to tie on an amulet  
3. to engage in with earnestness  
applied chiefly to improper  
or unimportant pursuits  
and only in colloquial usage  
4. [in medicine.]  
to tie a string a certain herbs  
c.  
that are to be plucked up in order to dispel a curse pronounced on them  
5. to be gin to read a purana at a temple